gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Celtics 114, Knicks 98
gameRecap.excerpt: The Celtics ended the game on a 23-10 run as they defeated the Knicks, 114-98. Jayson Tatum led the Celtics with 35 points, seven assists, and six rebounds as Jaylen Brown (22 points, six assists, five rebounds) and Kristaps Porzingis (21 points) totaled 43 points. Jalen Brunson led the Knicks with 26 points and four assists as Julius Randle totaled 25 points, nine rebounds, and five assists. The Celtics have now won three-straight games and improve to 8-2 on the year (5-0 at home) as the Knicks move to 5-5 on the year.
